      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): bound body-less MCP HTTP text responses",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\n`ensureGlobalFetchResponse` in the MCP HTTP fetch wrapper reads the entire response body via `await response.text()` for body-less `Response`-like objects. This path exists so the MCP SDK can parse OAuth error text from foreign response implementations (introduced in #91451), but it has no size limit. A buggy or malicious peer that returns a body-less response with an oversized `text()` payload can force the runtime to buffer the whole string into memory — an OOM vector. This is the same class of boundary resilience issue fixed for provider response reads by Alix-007 in #96903, #96886, and similar.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.ts`: added `MCP_HTTP_MAX_TEXT_RESPONSE_BYTES = 1 * 1024 * 1024`. `ensureGlobalFetchResponse` now:\r\n  - checks `Content-Length` before calling `response.text()` and returns a null body if it exceeds the cap;\r\n  - checks the returned text length after the call and returns a null body if it exceeds the cap;\r\n  - preserves the existing small-OAuth-error-body behavior below the cap.\r\n- `src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.test.ts`: added a regression test that uses the same `ForeignResponse` pattern from #91451 but with a 1 MiB + 1 byte `text()` payload, asserting the response body is dropped.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- **Behavior addressed**: A body-less MCP HTTP response with an oversized `text()` payload must not be buffered whole; the wrapper must drop the body while preserving status/headers.\r\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Node v22 workspace, using the exported production `buildMcpHttpFetch` against a mock undici runtime that returns a `ForeignResponse`-like object.\r\n- **Exact steps**: `node --import tsx /tmp/proof-mcp-http-fetch.mts` constructs a body-less 400 response whose `text()` returns 1 MiB + 1 byte, calls `buildMcpHttpFetch(...)(...)` and prints the resulting status and body presence.\r\n- **Observed result after fix**: `status=400 body=null`. Before the fix the same script printed `status=400 body=present`, meaning the oversized text was being forwarded into the returned `Response`.\r\n- **What was not tested**: A live MCP OAuth server was not hit; the proof uses the same `ForeignResponse` pattern the existing regression test uses, and the in-repo Vitest locks both the happy path and the oversized path.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\nTerminal proof (real production `buildMcpHttpFetch`, oversized `ForeignResponse`):\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-mcp-http-fetch.mts\r\nstatus=400 body=null\r\n```\r\n\r\nNegative control (temporary revert to `origin/main`):\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ git checkout origin/main -- src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.ts\r\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-mcp-http-fetch.mts\r\nstatus=400 body=present\r\n$ git checkout HEAD -- src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.ts\r\n```\r\n\r\nFocused Vitest:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.test.ts --run\r\n\r\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\r\n      Tests  11 passed (11)\r\n   Duration  2.50s\r\n```\r\n\r\nType checks:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ pnpm tsgo:core      # exit 0\r\n$ pnpm tsgo:core:test # exit 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/mcp-http-fetch-bound-text-read",
